cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DC, cs.NE 

This paper investigates the impact of batch size on the performance of GPUs and TPUs during training and inference phases of deep neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves experiments with standard datasets, which could place it in cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-categories.
